claim: Flublok contains 45 micrograms (mcg) of HA per strain vs 15 mcg of HA per strain in a standard-dose influenza vaccine.
explanation: A table displaying the incidence of solicited local and systemic adverse events (e.g., pain, erythema, headache, myalgia) reported in clinical studies, with columns showing percentages (e.g., <1, 1, 2, 3, 5, 6) for different study vaccine groups. does not support the claim because the image presents adverse event data and contains no information on hemagglutinin (HA) microgram content per strain for Flublok or standard-dose influenza vaccines.
